<div style="padding: 10px;">
    <p style="line-height: 1.6; font-size: 1.1em;">
        The grid below displays all existing <strong>Capable to Promise (CTP)</strong> requests for the selected planning area. These requests represent potential jobs that need to be assessed for their feasibility based on current resources and scheduling.
    </p>
    <p style="line-height: 1.6; font-size: 1.1em;">
        Each request is evaluated to determine whether it can be fulfilled on time, considering factors like <strong>inventory availability</strong>, <strong>required materials</strong>, and <strong>scheduling constraints</strong>.
    </p>
    <p style="line-height: 1.6; font-size: 1.1em;">
        To initiate a new CTP simulation:
    </p>
    <ol style="padding-left: 20px; margin-top: 10px;">
        <li>Select a row from the grid to populate the CTP Estimate tile with relevant product information.</li>
        <li>Customize the request by entering additional required and optional settings.</li>
        <li>Once ready, click <strong>"Submit"</strong> to perform the CTP simulation.</li>
    </ol>
    <p style="line-height: 1.6; font-size: 1.1em;">
        The simulation will generate a detailed result, indicating whether the order can be completed on time or if an alternative delivery date is necessary.
    </p>
</div>
